    "Imbalance occurs when the number of samples belonging to one class or class (majority class[es]) significantly surpasses the number of objects in another class or class (minority class[es]) 45, 46.",
    "Despite real-world data often being imbalanced, most models assume uniform distribution and complete input information 47.",
    "Thus, a nonuniform input data distribution poses difficulties when training models.",
    "The minority class occurrences are rare, and classification rules for predicting them are often ignored.",
    "As a result, test samples belonging to the minority classes are misclassified more frequently compared with test samples from the predominant classes."
  ],
